==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[mona|mōna]] + [[dæg|dæġ]].  Corresponding to Old Frisian ''mōnendei'', Old High German ''[[mānetac]]'' (Dutch ''[[maandag]]'', German ''[[Montag]]''), Old Norse ''mánadagr'' (Icelandic ''[[mánudagur]]'', Swedish ''[[måndag]]'').

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'mo:nandæj/

===Noun===
